{{Infobox settlement |name = Falaleu |other_name = |native_name = |settlement_type =Village |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |pushpin_map =Wallis |pushpin_label_position =right |pushpin_map_caption =Location in Wallis Island |pushpin_map_size=300 |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|France}} |subdivision_type1 = Territory |subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Wallis and Futuna|local}} |subdivision_type2 = Island |subdivision_name2 = [[Wallis (island)|Wallis]] |subdivision_type3 = Chiefdom |subdivision_name3 = [[Uvea (Wallis and Futuna)|Uvea]] |subdivision_type4 = District |subdivision_name4 = [[Hahake District|Hahake]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |population_as_of = 2008 |population_footnotes = |population_total =626 |population_density_km2 = |timezone = [[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]] |utc_offset = |coordinates = {{coord|13|17|36|S|176|10|54|W|region:WF|display=inline,title}} |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |elevation_ft = |website = |footnotes = }} '''Falaleu''' is a village in [[Wallis and Futuna]]. It is located in [[Hahake District]] on the east coast of [[Wallis Island]]. Its population according to the 2008 census was 626 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insee.fr/fr/themes/detail.asp?ref_id=poplegalescom&page=recensement/poplegalescom/popvillwallisetfutuna.htm|title=Population municipale des villages des îles Wallis et Futuna (recensement 2008)|publisher=[[INSEE]]|accessdate=10 June 2011}}</ref>
==References== {{Reflist}}
{{Villages in Wallis and Futuna}}
[[Category:Populated places in Wallis and Futuna]]
{{WallisFutuna-geo-stub}}

The '''geology of [[Sint Maarten]]''' consists of [[andesite]] [[tuff]] and tuff [[breccia]] from the middle and late [[Eocene]], intruded by hypabyssal basalt, quartz [[diorite]] and younger andesite. Volcanic activity led to metamorphism of many rocks and the tilting and folding of the tuff series. Limestone and [[marl]] was later unconformably deposited atop the eroded volcanic rocks as volcanic activity shifted elsewhere.<ref name="geoscienceworld">{{cite web|url=https://pubs.geoscienceworld.org/gsa/gsabulletin/article-abstract/64/1/65/4529|title=Geology of St. Bartholomew, St. Martin, and Anguilla, Lesser Antilles &#124; GSA Bulletin|website=GeoScienceWorld|accessdate=2018-11-09}}</ref>
==References== {{reflist}} {{North America topic|Geology of}}
[[Category:Geology of the Netherlands Antilles|Sint Maarten]] [[Category:Geology by country| Sint Maarten]] [[Category:Geography of Sint Maarten]]

