{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Kanalla Falls | photo = | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = | map = South Australia | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|31|29|52|S|138|30|43|E|region:AU-SA_type:waterbody_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Kanalla Falls (SA)|feature=SA0013723}}</ref><ref name=sagaz>{{cite web|title=Kanalla Falls |url=http://www.placenames.sa.gov.au/pno/searchResults.jsf |work=South Australian State Gazeteer |publisher=[[Government of South Australia]]: Department for Transport, Energy and Infrastructure |date=30 November 2009 |accessdate=31 May 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203005438/http://www.placenames.sa.gov.au/pno/searchResults.jsf |archivedate= 3 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> | location = [[Flinders Ranges]], [[South Australia]] | type = | elevation = {{convert|433|m}}<ref name=bonzle/> {{AHD}} | height = {{Convert|64|-|79|m}}<ref name=bonzle>{{cite web|url=http://www.bonzle.com/c/a?a=p&p=253813&cmd=sp|title=Map of Kanalla Falls, SA|work=Bonzle Digital Atlas of Australia|date=|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref> | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = Edeowie Creek | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Kanalla Falls''', a [[waterfall]] on the Edeowie Creek, is located in the [[Flinders Ranges]] in the [[Australia]]n [[States and territories of Australia|state]] of [[South Australia]].
Situated within the [[Flinders Ranges National Park]] approximately {{convert|44|km}} north of the village of {{SAcity|Hawker}} and {{convert|380|km}} north of [[Adelaide]], the waterfalls descend from below [[St Mary Peak]] and a range of other mountains at an elevation of {{convert|433|m}} [[Australian Height Datum|above sea level]]; falling in the range of {{Convert|64|-|79|m}} into the [[Wilpena Pound]] valley below.<ref name=bonzle/>
